author: The Peninsula
title: Saudi tourism chairman tours Qatar National Museum
text:
(MENAFN - The Peninsula)Prince Sultan bin Salman bin Abdulaziz Al Saud Chairman Saudi Commission for Tourism and Antiquities with other officials during a visit to Qatar National Museum. Doha: Prince Sultan bin Salman bin Abdulaziz Al Saud Chairman Saudi Commission for Tourism and Antiquities yesterday visited Qatar National Museum under construction. 

He was received by Qatar Museums Board of Trustees Vice-Chairman Sheikh Hassan bin Mohammed Al Thani and briefed on the unique architectural design of the museum inspired by the “Desert Rose”. 

Prince Sultan also toured the Old Palace of Sheikh Abdullah bin Jassim Al Thani in the centre of the museum. The museum is conceived and designed by French architect Jean Nouvel. 

QNA
